In PostgreSQL, that&#39;s just the `&amp;&amp;` operator. jOOQ doesn&#39;t support it natively, but as always, you can easily add support yourself using [plain SQL templating][1]:

```java
condition.and(&quot;not ({0} &amp;&amp; {1})&quot;, 
    PRODUCT.RESTRICTED_DELIVERY_REGIONS,

    // Pass the bind value using the DataType of the generated column,
    // for convenience
    val(criteria.getRestrictedRegionsList(), PRODUCT.RESTRICTED_DELIVERY_REGIONS)
);
```

This is assuming your list is already an array. If it isn&#39;t you&#39;ll have to convert it to an array, first.

As [everything you do with jOOQ is effectively dynamic SQL][2], you can create a small library for such vendor-specific functions, e.g.

```java
public static &lt;T&gt; Condition containsAny(
    Field&lt;T[]&gt; left,
    T... right
) {
    return containsAny(left, val(right, left));
}

public static &lt;T&gt; Condition containsAny(
    Field&lt;T[]&gt; left,
    Field&lt;T[]&gt; right
) {
    return DSL.condition(&quot;({0} &amp;&amp; {1})&quot;, left, right);
}
```


  [1]: https://www.jooq.org/doc/latest/manual/sql-building/plain-sql-templating/
  [2]: https://www.jooq.org/doc/latest/manual/sql-building/dynamic-sql/

